Texas Chukwu, Abuja: In continuation of intensive patrol across the states following a report on criminal hideouts, on Sunday 11 March 2018 troops of Headquarters Commands Army Record supported by Army Headquarters Special Forces conducted a raid operation at Irovochinomi and Egee communities within Okene Local Government Area of Kogi State. During the operation one of the prime suspect by name Mohammed Bashir a member of the gang that allegedly killed Corporal Mamman of Army Headquarters Special Forces on 27 February 2018, was apprehended and the following items were recovered, 2 AK 47 rifles with registration number 58008731 and 45 rounds of 7.62mm special was recovered. <img src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/IMG-20180311-WA0016-420x420.jpg" alt="" width="420" height="420" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-59671" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/IMG-20180311-WA0016-420x420.jpg 420w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/IMG-20180311-WA0016-150x150.jpg 150w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/IMG-20180311-WA0016-768x768.jpg 768w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/IMG-20180311-WA0016-720x720.jpg 720w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/IMG-20180311-WA0016.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" /> A follow up on the operation led to recovery of additional 2 AK 47 rifles. Pictures of the suspect and the items recovered are attached. The public are once again reminded that the operation still in progress. A.M Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. With a decade experience in Television journalism, and a graduate of University of Maiduguri. Tanimu also produces TV shows with NTA when not on Social media.